oduction costs are formidable, the churn is seasonal, the tech stack is ext=
endable but expensive, and the content, itself, is live and therefore ephem=
eral. =E2=80=9CAll of this,=E2=80=9D MoffettNathanson writes=E2=80=94=E2=80=
=9Cthe impact of ESPN Flagship, whether Venu still plans to launch, the fut=
ure of Disney+ and Hulu either as standalone or integrated services, bundle=
s and unbundling=E2=80=94leads to the key question at the heart of investor=
 concerns: what are Disney=E2=80=99s long-term streaming margins?=E2=80=9D

From the Cheap Seats

On the =E2=80=98Varsity=E2=80=99 podcast with John Smoltz: =E2=80=9CAmazing=
 interview. Very interesting to hear his take on pitchers going longer than=
 six innings. His idea on the D.H. playing as long as the starting pitcher =
was in the game was beyond intriguing. [Smoltz] is the ideal person to ask,=
 since he was an incredible closer and starter. The detail of him trying ou=
t for Michigan State point guard alongside Andre Rison was an anecdote I ha=
d never heard before.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94A producer, via LinkedIn ( https://=
www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7256372017837281281/?utm_campa=
ign=3DThe+Varsity+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2810%2F28%2F24%29&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io=
 )

On Unrivaled rivals: =E2=80=9CHow did two
groups of people in the sports business at very high levels both announce n=
ew companies in sports with darned close to the same name, within a very cl=
ose time of each other: Unrivaled women=E2=80=99s basketball and Unrivaled =
youth sports.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94A sports media executive who knows the scor=
e

On Steve =E2=80=9CBalls=E2=80=9D Ballmer: =E2=80=9CLittle did I know that t=
he manager of my high school=E2=80=99s basketball team, the Detroit Country=
 Day School Yellowjackets, would someday own a basketball team himself. It=
=E2=80=99s been great to follow =E2=80=98Balls=E2=80=99 (his politically in=
correct high-school nickname) career from Microsoft to the Clippers, and I =
can assure you that his personality is exactly the same as it was 50+ years=
 ago.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94A former media executive

On Marchand=E2=80=99s next career move: =E2=80=9CJason Kelce=E2=80=99s late=
-night show could be Marchand=E2=80=99s big break in the role of a modern E=
d McMahon. (Google it, kids.)=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94A cable
guy

On what to do in Ireland: =E2=80=9CHave a great trip in Ireland! You may wa=
nt to consider watching a hurling or camogie game. It=E2=80=99s a pretty fu=
n niche sport (in my very biased opinion), and apparently it was an inspira=
tion for baseball.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94A Varsity subscriber

Sl=C3=A1n until Thursday,
John

